; Reconvergent table-less plumbing (v3-spec section 1.4 / DeltaRelationalIR OQ):
; the DR-IR branch discovery must reproduce the old path-copying DFS's
; per-PATH branch multiset on a DIAMOND of table-less plumbing, where the
; memoized worklist could otherwise collapse reconvergent paths to one.
;
; A single differential source `src(X, Y)` fans out through three CMP-filtered
; plumbing paths that carry NO table of their own and RECONVERGE at the union
; feeding `mid`, then `mid` fans out again through two more CMP paths that
; reconverge at the union feeding `sink` -- a diamond at least two deep. Each
; CMP branch (`X < Y`, `X > Y`, `X != Y`, ...) is a distinct table-less path
; from the source member view to the reconvergence point, so the old DFS
; records one BranchChain per path and the memoized form must too.
;
; Differential message + query per the corpus contract; keep suite-sized.

#message src(u64 X, u64 Y) @differential.

#local mid(u64 X, u64 Y).
#local sink(u64 X).

#query sink_q(free u64 X).

; First diamond: src fans out through three CMP paths into mid.
mid(X, Y) : src(X, Y), X < Y.
mid(X, Y) : src(X, Y), X > Y.
mid(X, Y) : src(X, Y), X != Y.

; Second diamond: mid fans out through two CMP paths into sink.
sink(X) : mid(X, Y), X < Y.
sink(X) : mid(X, Y), X != Y.

sink_q(X) : sink(X).
